---
description: Configuration-driven development. No magic numbers in code.
globs: ["src/**/*.py", "configs/**/*.yaml"]
alwaysApply: false
---

# Config-driven

- Anything that varies between runs lives in `configs/*.yaml`, validated by
  `psalm.config.settings.ExperimentConfig` (pydantic-settings + YAML).
- No magic numbers, paths, thresholds, or hyperparameters hard-coded in logic.
- Pre-registered go/no-go thresholds live in the `go_no_go` config block; changing
  one requires an ADR (`docs/decisions/`).
- The resolved config hash (`psalm.config.loader.config_hash`) is recorded with
  every run in the experiment ledger for reproducibility.
- Arm configs override only what differs from `configs/base.yaml` so experimental
  arms stay matched (the integrity gate verifies fairness).
